main event: Two orange lights were observed moving at jet speed without sound in the Dallas sky.
interesting points: The lights were seen traveling northwest and then southwest before moving southeast at approximately 1500 feet altitude., The sighting lasted around one minute., The observing technician, Mr. James Kelly, reported that the lights were brighter than any normal aircraft., The sighting involved additional witnesses, indicating a potential multiple-person observation., No additional physical evidence was reported regarding the sighting.
witness description: Mr. James Kelly, Technician Trainee at Gesl Telephone Company, and three other individuals.
